  "local_port": 57966,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I add more topics here in Quora?",
  "response": "Quora is a platform where users can ask questions, provide answers, and engage in discussions on a wide variety of topics. If you want to add or suggest new topics on Quora, here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### 1. **Ask a Question with a New Topic**\n   - When you ask a question on Quora, you can include topics that are relevant to your question.\n   - If the topic you add doesn\u2019t already exist on Quora, the system may create a new topic based on your input.\n\n   **Steps**:\n   - Click on the \"Add Question\" button.\n   - Type your question and add relevant topics in the \"Add Topics\" section.\n   - If the topic is new, Quora will create it automatically.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Suggest a New Topic**\n   - If you notice that a specific topic is missing, you can suggest it to Quora.\n\n   **Steps**:\n   - Go to the \"Topics\" page (https://www.quora.com/topics).\n   - Scroll down and click on \"Suggest a Topic.\"\n   - Fill out the form with the topic name, description, and why it\u2019s relevant.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Edit Existing Questions or Topics**\n   - If you\u2019re adding a new topic to an existing question, you can edit the question to include it.\n\n   **Steps**:\n   - Find the question you want to update.\n   - Click on the three dots (...) next to the question.\n   - Select \"Edit Question\" and add the new topic.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Engage with the Quora Community**\n   - Participate in discussions and encourage others to explore new topics. If multiple users engage with a specific topic, Quora may prioritize it.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Follow and Contribute to Related Topics**\n   - Follow related topics and contribute high-quality content. This helps Quora\u2019s algorithm recognize the need for niche or new topics.\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps, you can help expand the range of topics available on Quora and contribute to a more diverse and engaging community!",
